  <front>
   <head>An EPIGRAM. Written to the Duke de Noailles.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quintet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">the Concern which You express,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That uncall'd  will possess</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Your House and Coach, both Day and Night;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And that  was haunted less</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">By  restless Spright.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quintet">
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With Fifteen Thousand Pound a Year,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Do You complain, You cannot bear</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">An Ill, You may so soon retrieve?</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Good , faith, is modester</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">By much, than You believe.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quintet">
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Lend Him but fifty ;</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And You shall never see Him more:</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Take the Advice; .</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why do the Gods indulge our Store,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">But to secure our Rest?</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
